<p><span class="switcher-label" style="display:none"><span class="randomSlideshow-sr-only">Image 36</span></span>The <a href="/wiki/Spine_(bookbinding)" class="mw-redirect" title="Spine (bookbinding)">spine</a> of the book is an important aspect in book design, especially in the cover design. When the books are stacked up or stored in a shelf, the details on the spine is the only visible surface that contains the information about the book. In a book store, it is often the details on the spine that attract the attention first. (from <b><a href="/wiki/Book_design" title="Book design">Book design</a></b>)
